&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vision Scientist - Band 5 (1WTE fixed term - 12 months)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We seek an empathic and enthusiastic band 5 vision scientist in clinical paediatric visual electrophysiology. This is a fixed 12 month post covering a career break in the Tony Kriss Visual Electrophysiology Unit, part of the Ophthalmology department of Great Ormond Street Hospital for Children NHS Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting chance to experience the scope of paediatric electrophysiology in a tertiary referral hospital and develop skills in visual electrophysiology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post-holder will assist a team of clinical scientists to carry out visual electrophysiological tests in young children. This position will suit someone who enjoys teamwork, is very flexible and resilient and scientifically interested. The job is demanding, but very rewarding. We will provide training and supervision within the unit to support the post-holder with the skills and knowledge they need to fulfil the core job specification and assist clinical service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
